Supervisor Behaviour for Web Prolog — Test Package
===================================================

Files:
  actor.pl            — actor runtime
  server.pl           — minimal server behaviour
  supervisor_actor.pl — supervisor behaviour
  supervisor_actor_tests.pl  — test suite (16 tests)

Quick start:

  Place all four .pl files in the same directory, then:

  $ swipl actor.pl server.pl supervisor_actor.pl supervisor_actor_tests.pl -g run_tests -g halt

  Or interactively:

  $ swipl
  ?- [actor, server, supervisor, supervisor_actor_tests].
  ?- run_tests.

  To see supervisor debug output:

  ?- debug(supervisor).
  ?- run_tests.

What the tests cover:

  1.  Basic startup and which_children introspection
  2.  one_for_one: crashed child restarts, sibling unchanged
  3.  temporary child: removed after crash, not restarted
  4.  transient child: not restarted on normal exit
  5.  one_for_all: one crash restarts all children
  6.  rest_for_one: crash restarts crashed child and successors
  7.  Dynamic start_child (including duplicate rejection)
  8.  Dynamic terminate_child and delete_child
  9.  Dynamic restart_child
  10. Server child under supervision (fridge from Chapter 5)
  11. count_children introspection
  12. Restart intensity: supervisor shuts down when exceeded
  13. Nested supervision: outer supervisor manages inner supervisor
  14. Server stopped via server_stop: permanent child restarts
  15. Server stopped via server_stop: transient child does NOT restart

Known issues / not yet implemented:

  - simple_one_for_one strategy
  - Logging / SASL-style event reports
